SoftwareInstance.name: SoftwareInstance
SoftwareInstance.description: An identified item of software running on a host
SoftwareInstance.long_description: An instance of a software entity running in the environment. Often corresponds to one or more processes running on a Host.

attrs.name: short_name
attrs.description: Short name of the Software Instance

attrs.name: cloud
attrs.description: When set, this flag indicates that the Software instance runs directly on a cloud service

attrs.name: instance
attrs.description: The product's own name for this instance

attrs.name: cluster_id
attrs.description: The internal identifier of the cluster this element is contributing to

attrs.name: cluster_name
attrs.description: The internal name of the cluster this element is contributing to

attrs.name: listening_ports
attrs.description: Ports this element is configured to listen on

attrs.name: publisher
attrs.description: The publisher of the Software Instance. Only populated in cases that a Pattern identifies products from more than one publisher. This information is normally found in the Pattern node's publishers attribute.

attrs.name: product
attrs.description: The product name. Only populated in cases that a Pattern identifies more than one product. This information is normally found in the Pattern node's products attribute.

attrs.name: age_count
attrs.description: The number of consecutive successful (positive) or failed (negative) times the Software Instance has been seen during host scans

attrs.name: last_update_success
attrs.description: The time at which a scan was last successfully associated with this Software Instance

attrs.name: last_update_failure
attrs.description: The time at which a scan associated with this Software Instance failed

attrs.name: configipedia
attrs.description: Link to Discovery Content Reference page (formerly Configipedia)

attrs.name: __explicit_removal
attrs.description: Pattern that has taken over removal in place of standard removal

attrs.name: _shared
attrs.description: When set, this flag indicates that the Software Instance should always be regarded as shared or not shared for purposes of visualization and service modelling. This is a user controlled flag.
